org.mozilla.gecko.annotation

Annotation Type WrapForJNI


  • @Target(value={TYPE,FIELD,METHOD,CONSTRUCTOR})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface WrapForJNI
    This annotation is used to tag methods that are to have wrapper methods generated. Such methods will be protected from destruction by ProGuard, and allow us to avoid writing by hand large amounts of boring boilerplate.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String calledFrom
      The thread that the method will be called from.
      String dispatchTo
      The thread that the method call will be dispatched to.
      String exceptionMode
      Action to take if member access returns an exception.
      boolean noLiteral
      Generate a getter instead of a literal.
      boolean skip
      Skip this member when generating wrappers for a whole class.
      String stubName
      Optional parameter specifying the name of the generated method stub.

    • Element Detail

      • skip

        public abstract boolean skip
        Skip this member when generating wrappers for a whole class.
        Default:
        false

      • stubName

        public abstract String stubName
        Optional parameter specifying the name of the generated method stub. If omitted, the capitalized name of the Java method will be used.
        Default:
        ""

      • exceptionMode

        public abstract String exceptionMode
        Action to take if member access returns an exception. - "abort" will cause a crash if there is a pending exception. - "ignore" will not handle any pending exceptions; it is then the caller's responsibility to handle exceptions. - "nsresult" will clear any pending exceptions and return an error code; not supported for native methods.
        Default:
        "abort"

      • calledFrom

        public abstract String calledFrom
        The thread that the method will be called from. One of "any", "gecko", or "ui". Not supported for fields.
        Default:
        "any"

      • dispatchTo

        public abstract String dispatchTo
        The thread that the method call will be dispatched to. - "current" indicates no dispatching; only supported value for fields, constructors, non-native methods, and non-void native methods. - "gecko" indicates dispatching to the Gecko XPCOM (nsThread) event queue. - "gecko_priority" indicates dispatching to the Gecko widget (nsAppShell) event queue; in most cases, events in the widget event queue (aka native event queue) are favored over events in the XPCOM event queue. - "proxy" indicates dispatching to a proxy function as a function object; see widget/jni/Natives.h.
        Default:
        "current"

      • noLiteral

        public abstract boolean noLiteral
        Generate a getter instead of a literal. Only supported for static final fields.
        Default:
        false
